description:
Julie's search for the truth leads her to Salome just in time to see all hell break loose as a piece of Wonderland escapes out into the real world threatening to kill them both. Together they face the insanity given form and manage to defeat the creature but if they are to survive the madness they will to have to visit the one place where all the horror began...where the Red Knight is waiting for them both.

The countdown to the Wonderland ongoing series continues.

Note: The Queen of Spades only appears on the cover.

description:
Throughout his whole life, Peter Stanchek has been confused by his strange powers and their effect on those closest to him. Now, having abandoned everything he knows, Peter has escaped to the confines of Toyo Harada’s Harbinger Foundation where his new training will temper his body, torture his mind and reawaken the horrors of his past. But is all of this truly giving Peter more control over his power? Or simply making him far more dangerous than he’s ever been before?

Includes a sneak preview of X-O Manowar # 5.

description: Detective Comics #526, Detective Comics #537

The conclusion of the two part adaptation of the classic F.W. Murnau silent film which was derived from Bram Stoker's Dracula novel. Painted and done in expressionistic style to match the original intent of the film, the comic series pays homage to the great film.

Tinker Bell's oldest friend Peter Pan and her oldest enemy Captain Hook both guest star in the newest volume of the Cyblis Award-nominated series. Containing four magical stories jam-packed with rare appearances by some of the most beloved Disney characters, including the bumbling pirate Mr. Smee and the fairies of Pixie Hollow who have never appeared in comics - until now!

Available in hardcover and softcover.
name: Tinker Bell and her Stories for a Rainy Day

description:
Charles Biro’s Little Wise Guys were no ordinary comic book kid gang. Though illustrated in a straightforward, line-drawn style, their stories were complex, engrossing dramas packed with plot and subtle character delineation. This debut issue features two classic reprints from the original Lev Gleason Publications comics out of the Golden Age. “Heroes By The Dozen”, illustrated by Norman Maurer, and “Jumped Or Fell”, both originally seen in Daredevil #72, 1950. Plus, a text overview of the comic book history of Daredevil and the Little Wise Guys, by Bill Black. Color cover based on an illustation by Norman Maurer, interiors are black and white with graytones. 36 pages, printed in 1989.

"Heroes by the Dozen":

The Little Wise Guys enter the Second Annual Boy Hero Contest. Pee Wee becomes convinced that he can win it through strategy.

"Jumped or Fell":

After aiding a motorist change a flat tire, the Little Wise Guys are invited on a trip to a ski resort. The holiday turns sour after the team gets on the trail of a dangerous murderer.

More adventures of Charlie Biro’s Little Wise Guys, leading off with a NEW,- never- before -seen story!! Young millionaire Bart Hill is “saved” from a mugging by The Little Wise Guys, who do not suspect he is really the costumed , boomerang-wielding Reddevil. VERY Biroesque story and art, written by Bill Black, and illustrated by Frank Turner and Rik Levins. Guest starring Kilroy, the reporter. Then, a pair of classic stories reprinted from vintage Golden Age issues of Lev Gleason’s Daredevil Comics- “Not So Easy Money”, illustrated by Nornman Maurer, and “Swimmer In The Night”. Cover is black, white and red-toned, interiors are black and white with graytones. 36 pages. Printed in 1990.

"Presenting... Reddevil"

A modern retelling of the Little Wise Guys first meeting with Reddevil.

"Not So' Easy Money"

The Little Wise Guys race against time to stop an elderly couple from giving their life savings to con artists.

"Swimmer in the Night"

While working as life guards at the beach, the Little Wise Guys stumble across a Soviet spy ring.

Funky Koval, Universs agency employee, declares private war against Stellar Fox corporation. In order to succeed, he has to act above the law. Koval's only allies in his fight for the fate of humanity are drolls - a mysterious race of aliens who have their own agenda.
name: Sam przeciw wszystkim

description:
The adventures of the Parr family continue in Disney/Pixar's THE INCREDIBLES. Mark Waid and Landry Walker take your favorite superheroes on a fearsome journey as Dash's suspicions that his teacher might be an alien take them from a parent/teacher conference to a ferocious battle at the earth's molten core.

Back Blurb

When Dash's impulsive action put his sister Violet in harm's way, Mr. and Mrs. Incredible ground him -- and take away his powers! Dejected and powerless, Dash stumbles into the knowledge that his teachers are actually mind controlling aliens from beyond the galaxy! But neither parent believes Dash. So when he finds that the sinister invaders have already compromised his family, can a powerless Dash get to the bottom of things... or is the earth doomed?
name: Volume 3

description:
Mrs. Incredible faces an unwelcome figure from her past plotting to destroy all of Europe; what's worse, they share a secret history she doesn't want Mr. Incredible finding out! Will the mysterious Mirage keep her secret, and can she be trusted to watch Mrs. Incredible's back? Meanwhile, Mr. Incredible and Frozone take it upon themselves to train Dash, and Violet makes a mistake that may have unexpected consequences for the Parr family! Available in Softcover and Hardcover editions.

Back Blurb

Blasts from the past!

When the Eiffel Tower explodes, only one woman can save the day: Mrs. Incredible! It's international adventure as she teams up with Mirage to take down the villain responsible -- but trouble brews when she discovers the villain's identity! Meanwhile, Mr. Incredible, Dash and Violet have their own troubles tracking don a mysterious thief. Follow them on a trail that will lead to superhero slugfests, giant robot dinosaurs, and a secret that could threaten to tear the entire family apart!
name: Volume 4

description:
The world's favorite family of superheroes faces its biggest challenge yet!

When the Underminer returns with a powerful new ally, The Incredibles are Metroville's only hope... just as long as the family can stop squabbling long enough to save the day! It's a high-stakes underground adventure filled with humor, suspense, angry gorillas and giant robots!
name: Volume 5

description:
The Phantom is puzzled by repeated references in the chronicles to “The Guardian of the Eastern Dark”. He goes to Old Man Mozz for advice. Mozz recites a story of lands beyond the Misty Peaks where people once worshipped Zaal, a god of Terror who demanded human sacrifice, but whose reign was stopped by the 9th Phantom.

Meanwhile, our Phantom is confronted with a new and lethal threat: drug peddlers have infiltrated the jungle to sell heroine to unsuspecting youths. Tracing the source to a chilling place he has recently heard about, the Phantom is forced to follow in his ancestor’s brave steps...
name: Guardian Of The Eastern Dark

description: Doctor Lansing and his nerdy assistant Mona are researching Meriem's DNA to produce a serum that will hopefully give the citizens of Marshville a better chance to survive the dangers of a prehistoric world. Jealous of the attention that Meriem receives from an adoring Marshville and wanting her boyfriend Bruce all to herself, Mona takes a heavy dose of the prototype serum and seeks to discover if she is more than a match for Meriem. Look out! It's a rumble in the jungle and Marshville isn't big enough for both of them!
